 import MosesTokenizer\r\nmt = MosesTokenizer()\r\nmt.tokenize(\"My name is <unk>\")\r\n>>> ['My', 'name', 'is', '&lt;', 'unk', '&gt;']\r\n```\r\nSimilar for the hyphen e.g. in\r\n```python\r\nfrom sacremoses import MosesTokenizer\r\nmt = MosesTokenizer()\r\nmt.tokenize(\"tactical and real @-@ time gameplay\")\r\n>>> ['tactical', 'and', 'real', '@', '-', '@', 'time', 'gameplay']\r\n```\r\nI would expect that these items stay joined. Especially the `<unk>` token.\r\nIs this the expected behaviour?","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/alvations/sacremoses/issues/136/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/alvations/sacremoses/issues/136/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}